ed59eac3-7856-45cd-a185-84ebd6079968.1a3abd01-5608-434f-9257-c8e755f359c8.description=
Gets the string value of an LDAP objects named property.
Creates a collection if more than one property of the same name exists.
Continue to call this same operation for all values until No More Values is returned.

Input Parameters\:
host - Name or IP address of LDAP server to query.
DN - DN of object to get property.
propertyName - Name of property to get.
username - Name of user to connect to LDAP as.
password - Password of user.
useADAuth - Add this input and set to false if using a non AD LDAP server. If false, uses ServerBind instead of secure NTLM based bind.
port - Specify the port in case it is not the default one, or it is not specified in the host path.

Responses\:
value retrieved - The value was retrieved and set as the result (returnResult).
no more values - There are no more values in the collection.
failure - failed to complete operation (one of the reasons could be port validation failure).
ed59eac3-7856-45cd-a185-84ebd6079968.44eabc5c-e24a-421b-a8df-9075f07612be.description=Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings Inputs\: operator - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=). value1 - the first value. value2 - the second value. Returns\: The result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false. Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true. failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false. ed59eac3-7856-45cd-a185-84ebd6079968.7039c014-6b04-47b1-98e8-12d5ed16054c.description=Converts a list of numerical fields into a base 10 number. Inputs\: list - A list of numbers in the given base. delimiter - the delimiter for list. startIndex - The index to start reading the list from. Default is 0. endIndex - The index to start reading the list from. Default is end. base - The number base to convert from. Use 256 for bytes. reverse - A boolean value that reverses the list before processing it. If a list is not reversed bytes towards the end of the list are more significant than bytes towards the start. Returns\: The converted number. ed59eac3-7856-45cd-a185-84ebd6079968.91568ef8-e077-42b9-8faa-82cec77853a4.description=
Compares two strings lexigraphically.

Inputs\:
String1 - The first string.
String2 - The string to compare string 1 to.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true' then the compare is not case sensitive.

responses\:
before - If string 1 is alphabetically before string 2.
after - If string 1 is alphabetically after string 2.
same - If string 1 is alphabetically equal to string 2.
failure - If Something goes wrong.

ed59eac3-7856-45cd-a185-84ebd6079968.description=
Checks if a user is a direct member of an Active Directory group.

Inputs\:
host - The hostname of an Active Directory domain controller.
username - The username for the host.
password - The password for the username.
userDN - The DN of the user to check, for example\: CN\=John Doe,CN\=Users,DC\=Domain,DC\=com.
groupDN - The DN of the group to check, for example\: CN\=Domain Users,CN\=Users,DC\=Domain,DC\=com.

Responses\:
success - The userDN is a member of the groupDN.
failure - The userDN is not a direct member of the groupDN or an error occurred.
